    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-12-20T08:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-12-20T08:30:00-05:00" n="1117"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1117">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.9194/12–2054: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in India</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_KDD1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New Delhi</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-12-20T19:00:00+05:30"
                            >December 20, 1954—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>836. Fourth proposal for continuation US airlines service (<gloss target="#t_A1"
                        >A-</gloss>124)<note n="1" xml:id="d1117fn1">Dated Nov. 10, <ref
                            target="#pg_1773">p. 1773</ref>.</note> as modified by <gloss
                        target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss>s 716<note n="2" xml:id="d1117fn2">Dated
                        Dec. 10, <ref target="#pg_1790">p. 1790</ref>.</note> and 727<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d1117fn3">Dated Dec. 13, <ref target="#pg_1794">p.
                        1794</ref>.</note> presented this afternoon to Communications Minister
                        <persName corresp="#p_RJ1">Ram</persName>. An unsigned memo outlining
                    proposal together with letter making substantive points justifying consideration
                    left with Minister. Copy memo also transmitted Foreign Secretary. <persName
                        corresp="#p_RJ1">Ram</persName>’s initial reaction was that it difficult not
                    to terminate agreement since notice had already been given and there would be
                    great embarrassment if this rescinded. He would not however, close door and said
                    he would have to check with his advisers. I urged that prior any rejection in
                    writing I be given opportunity discuss matter with him further. He said this
                    would be done. I pointed out that it might be worthwhile for him to consider
                    benefit to <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> of not terminating agreement
                    since one of articles provided in principle for Indian airlines to fly to US. In
                    making this point I indicated this had probably been thought of before but might
                    be worthy of another look. <persName corresp="#p_RJ1">Ram</persName>, however,
                    did not modify his original reaction that termination would have to go
                    through.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_KDD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Kennedy</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
